    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      697.76,
      394.66,
      711.76
    ],
    "text": "he was connected via the Zoom platform from prison.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      265.61,
      35.25,
      337.69,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0183/25",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "4 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      88.32,
      527.17,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "At the very outset of the argument, the Learned Counsel for the Appellant",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      109.56,
      504.12,
      123.56
    ],
    "text": "informed this Court that the Appellant is only contesting the sentence.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      140.76,
      391.54,
      154.82
    ],
    "text": "The Facts of this case albeit briefly are as follows.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      171.72,
      527.17,
      185.72
    ],
    "text": "The prosecutrix was a mentally impaired woman who was living with her",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      192.96,
      527.13,
      206.96
    ],
    "text": "mother, who is PW1 in this case. As the Appellant is a relation of PW1 by",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      214.08,
      527.28,
      228.08
    ],
    "text": "marriage, using this opportunity, the Appellant had raped the victim. When",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      235.23,
      527.08,
      249.23
    ],
    "text": "he was indulging in sex with the victim forcibly, PW1 had come there and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      256.35,
      527.2,
      270.35
    ],
    "text": "had seen the incident. Seeing the arrival of PW1, the Appellant had run away",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      277.47,
      527.21,
      291.47
    ],
    "text": "from the scene. PW1 had immediately informed the incident to her sister who",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      298.59,
      527.25,
      312.59
    ],
    "text": "is living close by and when both had inquired about this from the Appellant,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      319.71,
      527.16,
      333.71
    ],
    "text": "the Appellant threatened them with death. Due to fear, she had not divulged",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      340.83,
      527.12,
      354.83
    ],
    "text": "this incident to anybody, but someone had called the Police Emergency Unit",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      361.95,
      454.66,
      375.95
    ],
    "text": "(119) and the police had commenced investigations thereafter.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      393.15,
      527.26,
      407.15
    ],
    "text": "The JMO who examined the victim opined that the she was subjected to rape.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      414.29,
      527.0,
      428.29
    ],
    "text": "He further opined after obtaining psychiatric opinion, that the victim was a",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      435.41,
      251.09,
      449.41
    ],
    "text": "mentally retarded woman.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      466.49,
      527.28,
      480.49
    ],
    "text": "The victim was 35 years old when she was raped by the Appellant. The",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      487.61,
      437.38,
      501.61
    ],
    "text": "Appellant was 43 years old when he committed this offence.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      518.81,
      527.05,
      532.81
    ],
    "text": "The judge takes several factors into account when deciding on a sentence,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      539.93,
      527.06,
      553.93
    ],
    "text": "including the circumstances surrounding the crime and the situation of the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      561.08,
      278.23,
      575.08
    ],
    "text": "person who committed the crime.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      592.16,
      527.18,
      606.16
    ],
    "text": "The sentence must be in proportion to the seriousness of the crime. The law",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      613.28,
      527.06,
      627.28
    ],
    "text": "establishes how serious a crime is by providing different sentences for",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      634.4,
      527.05,
      648.4
    ],
    "text": "different types of crimes. This means lighter sentences for less serious",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      655.52,
      527.13,
      669.52
    ],
    "text": "crimes and heavier sentences for more serious crimes. According to the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      676.64,
      444.1,
      690.64
    ],
    "text": "principle of fairness in sentencing, the sentence must be just.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      265.61,
      35.25,
      337.69,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0183/25",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "5 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      88.32,
      527.14,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "As in other countries, no sentencing guidelines have been formulated in our",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      109.56,
      527.17,
      123.56
    ],
    "text": "jurisdiction. Therefore, sentencing falls within the prerogative of the court",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      130.68,
      192.05,
      144.68
    ],
    "text": "in our jurisdiction.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      161.76,
      527.25,
      175.76
    ],
    "text": "In this case the Learned High Court Judge had passed 20 years rigorous",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      182.88,
      527.18,
      196.88
    ],
    "text": "imprisonment on the count of rape. The Learned Counsel for the Appellant",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      204.0,
      465.94,
      218.0
    ],
    "text": "submits that this is not a case to impose the maximum sentence.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      235.23,
      527.05,
      249.23
    ],
    "text": "When sentencing in individual cases, the court must strike a balance",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      256.35,
      527.18,
      270.35
    ],
    "text": "between the seriousness of the offence as reflected in the maximum sentence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      277.47,
      527.28,
      291.47
    ],
    "text": "available under the law and the seriousness of the actual acts of the person.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      339.75,
      527.22,
      353.75
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Attorney General v H.N.Silva 57 NLR 121 the Court held",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      360.87,
      109.7,
      374.87
    ],
    "text": "that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      391.95,
      526.66,
      406.01
    ],
    "text": "\" A Judge should, in determining the proper sentence, first consider the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      413.09,
      526.64,
      427.15
    ],
    "text": "gravity of the offence as it appears from the nature of the act itself and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      434.21,
      526.72,
      448.27
    ],
    "text": "should have regard to the punishment provided in the Penal Code or",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      455.33,
      526.92,
      469.39
    ],
    "text": "other statute under which the offender is charged. He should also",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      476.45,
      526.81,
      490.51
    ],
    "text": "regard the effect of the punishment as a deterrent and consider to what",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      497.57,
      526.64,
      511.63
    ],
    "text": "extent it will be effective. If the offender held a position of trust or",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      518.69,
      526.7,
      532.75
    ],
    "text": "belonged to a service which enjoys the public confidence that must be",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      539.93,
      526.85,
      553.99
    ],
    "text": "taken into account in assessing the punishment. The incidence of crimes",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      561.08,
      526.64,
      575.14
    ],
    "text": "of the nature of which the offender has been found to be guilty and the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      582.2,
      526.71,
      596.26
    ],
    "text": "difficulty of detection are also matters which should receive due",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      603.32,
      527.02,
      617.38
    ],
    "text": "consideration. The reformation of the criminal, though no doubt an",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      624.44,
      526.68,
      638.5
    ],
    "text": "important consideration, is subordinate to the others I have mentioned.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      645.56,
      526.71,
      659.62
    ],
    "text": "Where the public interest or the welfare of the State (which are",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      666.68,
      526.7,
      680.74
    ],
    "text": "synonymous) outweighs the previous good character, antecedents and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      687.8,
      399.94,
      701.86
    ],
    "text": "age of the offender, public interest must prevail. \"",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      265.61,
      35.25,
      337.69,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0183/25",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "6 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      119.52,
      527.16,
      133.52
    ],
    "text": "In the case of The Attorney General v Mendis [1995] 1 Sri L.R 138 it was",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      140.64,
      110.9,
      154.64
    ],
    "text": "held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      171.72,
      526.86,
      185.78
    ],
    "text": "\u201cIn assessing punishment, the judge should consider the matter of",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      192.84,
      526.66,
      206.9
    ],
    "text": "sentence both from the point of view of the public and the offender. The",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      214.08,
      526.8,
      228.14
    ],
    "text": "judge should first consider the gravity of the offence, as it appears from",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      235.23,
      527.03,
      249.29
    ],
    "text": "the nature of the act itself and should have regard to the punishment",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      256.35,
      526.78,
      270.41
    ],
    "text": "provided in the Penal Code or other Statute under which the offender is",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      277.47,
      526.72,
      291.53
    ],
    "text": "charged. He should also regard the effect of the punishment as a",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      298.59,
      526.68,
      312.65
    ],
    "text": "deterrent and consider to what extent it will be effective. The incidence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      319.71,
      526.93,
      333.77
    ],
    "text": "of crimes of the nature of which the offender has been found to be guilty",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      340.83,
      526.77,
      354.89
    ],
